          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>Single folio; Writing surface: paper (dyed pink); Shelfmark: 2016.369a-b; Qurʾānic Text: Q 10:26 - 10:27; 5  lines per page; Script style: Maġribī <hi rend="italic">mabsūṭ </hi>(for the <hi rend="italic">rasm</hi>);  Estimated date of production: Shortly before 650/1252; Provenance: Marrakesh. </p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>  </p>
              <p>This is a folio from the fourth volume of a Qurʾān originally in ten volumes, endowed by the penultimate Almohad caliph al-Murtaḍā to the tomb of one of his wives, in 650/1252. Eight of the original ten volumes are still kept in Marrakesh, Ibn Yūsuf Library, ms. 431. Another monumental Almohad Qurʾān, probably copied by the same calligrapher in the exact same style of Maġribī <hi rend="italic">mabsūṭ </hi>script, is in the Topkapı Palace Library, ms. R. 21–24.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>For further information, see the <ref target="https://www.cincinnatiartmuseum.org/art/explore-the-collection?id=24980683">website of the Cincinnati Art Museum</ref>. </p>
            </summary>
